Gunmen have reportedly shot and killed a boy just as they injured another in Orhunwhorhun Community, Udu Local Government Area of Delta State. The incident occurred late Saturday evening, DAILY POST reports. Details as to why the deceased was shot dead was still sketchy at the time of this report. The gunmen shot sporadically in the area before they left the community. Policemen from Ovwian/Aladja Division promptly evacuated the remains of the deceased. The Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe confirmed the incident in a telephone chat with our correspondent in Warri.